1
00:00:10,467 --> 00:00:12,733
<i>It seems like what happened
was too perfect.</i>

2
00:00:12,867 --> 00:00:15,800
<i>Because in our precinct,
almost everyone has converted.</i>

3
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:16,900
<i>There's already a rumor, right,</i>

4
00:00:17,033 --> 00:00:18,267
<i>that there was an abandoned
child?</i>

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,533
<i> We've found a contact.</i>

6
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:20,700
<i> Just be careful, Boss.</i>

7
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:22,567
<i>This world you're about
to enter is dangerous.</i>

8
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:25,000
<i>That Enriquez seems really
stubborn, Sir.</i>

9
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:26,033
<i> It's going to be hard.</i>

10
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:27,900
<i>She might find out
that Amo is your father.</i>

11
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:29,600
<i>Why do they look so much alike?</i>

12
00:00:29,733 --> 00:00:30,933
<i> Are they related?</i>

13
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:34,200
Sir, water, Sir?

14
00:00:35,833 --> 00:00:37,267
It's okay. I just choked.

15
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:39,933
You know the saying
when you choke,

16
00:00:40,067 --> 00:00:42,200
it means someone remembers...

17
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:46,733
Enriquez...

18
00:00:46,867 --> 00:00:49,033
We're already face to face
and you still remember me.

19
00:00:49,167 --> 00:00:50,800
Sir, I'm not thinking about you.

20
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:54,467
I was just wondering
if they were related.

21
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:56,267
They look so much alike.

22
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:57,567
You know,

23
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:01,833
just because you look alike it
doesn't mean you're related?

24
00:01:01,967 --> 00:01:05,467
Me, I'm mistaken
for Dennis Trillo.

25
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:06,567
"Dennis, Dennis!"

26
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:09,500
That person calls me that,
but he wishes!

27
00:01:09,667 --> 00:01:10,867
What is he? Lucky?

28
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,933
Does that mean we're related?

29
00:01:14,067 --> 00:01:18,700
So, the same goes for Amo
and Conde.

30
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:25,400
I'm just curious
because they do look alike.

31
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:30,200
You know, Tonyo's father looks
so far away from him

32
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:32,667
and he lives so far away.

33
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:34,367
He's from Canada, yes.

34
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:36,333
He has his own family.

35
00:01:36,467 --> 00:01:38,167
You know,
don't think about that.

36
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:39,333
Just think about what we're
going to have

37
00:01:39,467 --> 00:01:41,567
for appetizers later.

38
00:01:41,733 --> 00:01:43,800
What do you want? Salad? Nachos?

39
00:01:43,933 --> 00:01:46,400
No, Sir. I'm going home.
I'll go ahead. Bye.

40
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:57,233
We're not looking for trouble.

41
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:59,933
We just want to find out
where Mr. Teban is.

42
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,333
He's a police officer!

43
00:02:03,467 --> 00:02:05,333
You're not going to get out
of here alive.

44
00:02:05,467 --> 00:02:06,800
Hold him!

45
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:02,833
Hey! What?

46
00:03:02,967 --> 00:03:04,067
Put your hands up!

47
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:07,400
I said put your hands up!

48
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,533
Put your gun down.

49
00:03:10,867 --> 00:03:12,267
We're not afraid of that.

50
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:16,833
All I need is KaTeban.

51
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:18,933
That's me.

52
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:21,967
I'm Ka Teban.

53
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,433
Bok!

54
00:03:30,567 --> 00:03:31,167
Bok!

55
00:03:33,067 --> 00:03:33,767
Come on.

56
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:34,767
What happened to you guys?

57
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:35,967
It looks like you guys got
into a fight.

58
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:38,900
Bok, if you don't have anything
important to say,

59
00:03:39,033 --> 00:03:39,800
let's talk later.

60
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:42,000
Bok, Bok, Bok.

61
00:03:43,133 --> 00:03:45,000
This is important.

62
00:03:45,133 --> 00:03:46,867
Be careful with Enriquez.

63
00:03:48,433 --> 00:03:49,333
Why?

64
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:51,667
I was talking to her earlier.

65
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:55,867
She asked me if you
and Amo were related.

66
00:03:56,033 --> 00:03:59,100
Because she saw Amo's
old picture and your picture.

67
00:03:59,233 --> 00:04:00,100
She said they look alike.

68
00:04:01,567 --> 00:04:03,167
She has a feeling you two were
related.

69
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:11,333
Bok, are you riding
a motorcycle?

70
00:04:11,467 --> 00:04:13,200
Why are you wearing a jacket?

71
00:05:01,667 --> 00:05:02,933
Conde!

72
00:05:03,067 --> 00:05:04,733
How's your appointment?

73
00:05:04,867 --> 00:05:06,167
What happened to you?

74
00:05:07,233 --> 00:05:09,867
Well, Sir, we almost got
into trouble with Dizon there.

75
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,100
But we didn't get any info
on the contact.

76
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,300
You, Robles, Garcia?

77
00:05:17,267 --> 00:05:21,500
Sir, we've already tapped our
contacts in the military,

78
00:05:21,633 --> 00:05:26,500
but they don't know where
to buy this strychnine.

79
00:05:26,633 --> 00:05:28,533
They say it's been banned
for a long time.

80
00:05:29,867 --> 00:05:32,900
It seems like the guy who killed
Sonny has a special connection.

81
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:37,400
You, Enriquez,
do you have anything to add?

82
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:40,967
Nothing, Sir.

83
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:43,433
Didn't you do your research?

84
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:46,100
Sorry.

85
00:05:46,233 --> 00:05:47,833
That's because you've been busy
with something else.

86
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:50,500
That's enough.

87
00:05:52,633 --> 00:05:55,733
Garcia, Robles,
go back to where you came from.

88
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:58,933
Find out how to ship strychnine
to other countries.

89
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:05,300
Sir!

90
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:08,700
I don't like what you said
earlier.

91
00:06:10,667 --> 00:06:12,467
Forget about it, Enriquez.

92
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:16,200
Excuse me, Sir, but I won't
tolerate people disrespecting me

93
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:18,033
just because I'm a woman.

94
00:06:19,633 --> 00:06:22,367
I didn't say anything about you
being a woman.

95
00:06:24,767 --> 00:06:26,367
Why?

96
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:29,167
If I were a man, Sir, would you
be rude to me like that?

97
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,700
If you don't want people
to give remarks about you,

98
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:34,667
do your job.

99
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:37,600
Sir, just because I have nothing
to report,

100
00:06:37,733 --> 00:06:39,600
I'm not doing my job anymore.

101
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:42,833
Sir, I know I made a mistake

102
00:06:42,967 --> 00:06:47,767
but please don't insult me here
at my job.

103
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:50,000
Because I love being a police
officer.

104
00:06:57,367 --> 00:06:59,100
He's so annoying.

105
00:06:59,233 --> 00:07:00,533
He thinks he's good?

106
00:07:00,667 --> 00:07:03,467
Just chill. Watch your heart.

107
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:04,833
Let it go.

108
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:08,367
Bobby, you know,
speaking of hearts...

109
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:12,067
Aren't you just obsessed
with that Tonyo?

110
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:14,167
That's right, Abdul.

111
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:16,433
You know, you seem
so high-strung.

112
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,300
It's like you're deeply
affected.

113
00:07:18,433 --> 00:07:19,300
True.

114
00:07:19,433 --> 00:07:21,033
Besides, he looks like Amo,
doesn't he?

115
00:07:21,167 --> 00:07:22,133
True.

116
00:07:22,267 --> 00:07:24,033
What will I do with his looks
if he's grumpy?

117
00:07:24,167 --> 00:07:25,300
What? Always angry?

118
00:07:25,433 --> 00:07:27,333
Oh, my, grandchild, let it go.

119
00:07:27,467 --> 00:07:28,800
That's enough,
that's enough.

120
00:07:28,933 --> 00:07:31,700
You two, hurry up there,
take that upstairs.

121
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:33,067
Yes, Kapitana.

122
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,900
Yes, Kapitana.

123
00:07:35,033 --> 00:07:36,500
Hurry up.

124
00:07:40,267 --> 00:07:42,300
Bok, are you okay?

125
00:07:42,433 --> 00:07:43,300
Perfect.

126
00:07:48,467 --> 00:07:52,700
You know, Bok, you shouldn't
have argued with Enriquez.

127
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:55,600
You know what you should
have just done

128
00:07:55,733 --> 00:08:02,633
is to let me talk to her all she
needs is a little sweetness.

129
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,167
That's the thing.

130
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,033
The truth is,

131
00:08:10,167 --> 00:08:14,567
it's none of my business whether
she contributed or not.

132
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:18,567
I only vented my anger on
her about the case.

133
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:22,467
Are you angry about the case
or are you angry

134
00:08:22,633 --> 00:08:24,833
because I reported her to you?

135
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:26,467
But actually,

136
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:30,033
this case we're handling
is also really strange.

137
00:08:30,167 --> 00:08:33,600
I feel like this is where
my hair will turn gray.

138
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:43,633
I just need to solve this case,
Bok,

139
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:46,633
for Lara.

140
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:52,467
All right,
Kapitana you go first.

141
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,833
We'll bring these inside.

142
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:54,733
Oh, all right.

143
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,867
- Take that up.
- Okay, go.

144
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,900
Yes, Kapitana,
save us some food.

145
00:08:59,033 --> 00:08:59,633
Save us a lot.

146
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:00,167
Yes, please.

147
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:01,400
You'll be hungry.

148
00:09:01,533 --> 00:09:01,933
Come on.

149
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:04,900
Oh, don't. Ouch, it hurts.

150
00:09:05,033 --> 00:09:05,567
You're full of drama.

151
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:07,500
Hurry up. Get your baton.

152
00:09:07,633 --> 00:09:08,267
Oh, take that.

153
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,500
Oh, goodbye.

154
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:12,367
Captain, Bobby, be careful.

155
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:14,200
Yes. Come on. Move.

156
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,667
Why, Grandmother?

157
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:21,067
Why does it seem like you're
fuming mad at Conde?

158
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:25,533
Grandmother, you too?

159
00:09:25,667 --> 00:09:27,733
I don't know what you're talking
about.

160
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:30,867
What's different about your
precinct before?

161
00:09:33,467 --> 00:09:34,733
I get that, Grandmother.

162
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,333
They underestimated me there
too.

163
00:09:38,933 --> 00:09:40,500
This is different,
Grandmother.

164
00:09:41,067 --> 00:09:44,733
That's why I'm so upset
with Sir Tonyo

165
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:47,800
because he treats me like he's
the only person

166
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:49,333
who lost someone.

167
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:54,933
One more, Bok!

168
00:09:55,067 --> 00:09:55,933
Let's go.

169
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,833
Are you sure?

170
00:09:59,367 --> 00:10:00,467
- Yes!
- Go home!

171
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,900
I don't want to carry you.

172
00:10:02,067 --> 00:10:03,267
Bok, no...

173
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:03,833
nothing!

174
00:10:03,967 --> 00:10:05,367
I just had a...

175
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:07,200
Well, I'll take care of it.

176
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:08,333
My treat!

177
00:10:08,467 --> 00:10:11,767
You see? You're drunk!
You're offering to treat me.

178
00:10:11,900 --> 00:10:12,833
You're drunk.

179
00:10:12,967 --> 00:10:13,867
Am I drunk?

180
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,600
Yes, right?

181
00:10:15,733 --> 00:10:17,100
This is on you?
You'll pay for this?

182
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:19,400
Yes, I'll take care of that.

183
00:10:19,533 --> 00:10:20,533
But...

184
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:23,133
be careful, Bok.

185
00:10:23,267 --> 00:10:25,700
Maybe tomorrow,
I'll see you in the cell again.

186
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:26,733
I'll go there first.

187
00:10:26,867 --> 00:10:29,500
No. Go ahead, go home.
You're talking too much.

188
00:10:29,633 --> 00:10:30,200
Go ahead.

189
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:31,000
Be careful.

190
00:10:31,133 --> 00:10:32,933
Yes, I'll take care of it.

191
00:10:33,067 --> 00:10:34,700
Hey, hey, hey,
where are you going?

192
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:35,767
That's high.

193
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:37,833
You're drunk!
I'm just kidding you.

194
00:10:37,967 --> 00:10:38,767
- You're something else.
- I'll go this way.

195
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:39,700
Okay, Bok!

196
00:10:39,833 --> 00:10:40,800
Okay.

197
00:10:54,367 --> 00:10:56,667
You know, I've been worrying
about you so much.

198
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,600
Why, Grandmother?

199
00:10:58,733 --> 00:10:59,933
- Good evening, Captain.
- Good evening.

200
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:05,267
Well, maybe you'll
become a man-hater.

201
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,000
No, not at all. What's with you?

202
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:08,067
- Hello, Kapitana.
- Good evening.

203
00:11:08,233 --> 00:11:11,000
I know that not all men
are crazy.

204
00:11:11,133 --> 00:11:12,800
Bro, bro, bro, look at her.

205
00:11:12,933 --> 00:11:14,133
Wow...

206
00:11:14,267 --> 00:11:16,600
Ma'am is such a beautiful
policewoman.

207
00:11:16,733 --> 00:11:18,467
Ma'am, good evening!

208
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:21,100
I just wanted to say
that you're very pretty.

209
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:22,267
- Hey, stop.
- Grandmother...

210
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:24,900
- That's my granddaughter.
- Cheers, cheers.

211
00:11:26,867 --> 00:11:29,433
Miss, did you hear what he said?

212
00:11:29,567 --> 00:11:31,167
Excuse me, Ma'am, I'm sorry.

213
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:33,033
There, I have a witness.

214
00:11:33,167 --> 00:11:34,333
You're not from here, right?

215
00:11:34,467 --> 00:11:37,167
Do you know that because
of the rudeness you did to me,

216
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:39,200
you can go to jail
for six months?

217
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:40,767
And there inside the jail,

218
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,300
you can experience the rudeness
you did to me.

219
00:11:43,467 --> 00:11:45,200
What? You want?

220
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:46,733
That's my grandmother,
you're disrespecting her.

221
00:11:46,867 --> 00:11:48,500
She's the barangay captain here.

222
00:11:48,633 --> 00:11:50,133
Get out of here!

223
00:11:50,267 --> 00:11:50,933
- I'm sorry.
- Go there!

224
00:11:51,067 --> 00:11:52,300
- Sorry, sorry.
- I'm sorry.

225
00:11:52,433 --> 00:11:55,367
- Come on, come on.
- Excuse me.

226
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,933
Hey, my, my grandchild...

227
00:11:57,067 --> 00:12:01,067
If you only had a boyfriend,
no one would disrespect you.

228
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:05,433
Grandmother is something else.
I can handle those.

229
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:09,100
Baby!

230
00:12:09,233 --> 00:12:12,000
Your smile is so beautiful,
baby.

231
00:12:12,133 --> 00:12:13,367
You're so handsome.

232
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:14,933
You're shameless!

233
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:16,300
- Honey!
- You're shameless!

234
00:12:16,433 --> 00:12:17,333
What are you doing here?

235
00:12:17,467 --> 00:12:20,467
What are you doing?
You're flirting there.

236
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,533
And then you deny me,
you deny me, you deny me!

237
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:24,900
- You're such a womanizer!
- Sheila is just our friend!

238
00:12:25,033 --> 00:12:26,000
What friend?

239
00:12:26,133 --> 00:12:27,667
Don't make a scandal here.

240
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:28,700
What scandal,

241
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:30,133
it's you two are the ones who
made a mess,

242
00:12:30,267 --> 00:12:32,100
I'm the one making a scandal?

243
00:12:32,233 --> 00:12:34,567
Hey, excuse me, Miss!

244
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:37,367
Me, a pig?
Be ashamed of your size!

245
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:38,733
You have a thick face, Babalina!

246
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:40,133
- Hey!
- Hey!

247
00:12:40,267 --> 00:12:41,867
Don't talk to Sheila like that.

248
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,800
You're still defending
that thick face?

249
00:12:46,033 --> 00:12:47,533
Your face is thick!

250
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:48,533
You, you sycophant!

251
00:12:48,667 --> 00:12:51,133
- Oh, wait!
- That's enough!

252
00:12:51,267 --> 00:12:52,267
I said enough!

253
00:12:54,133 --> 00:12:57,000
Dude, we don't have to go
to this.

254
00:12:57,133 --> 00:12:58,867
Even if you reverse
the situation,

255
00:12:59,967 --> 00:13:01,367
it's wrong to hurt your wife.

256
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:02,067
Right!

257
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,533
Ah, is that so?

258
00:13:03,667 --> 00:13:04,633
Well, I'll hurt you instead!

259
00:13:05,667 --> 00:13:08,000
This is the only bottle
in the store.

260
00:13:08,133 --> 00:13:10,200
If this breaks,
you'll be accountable to me.

261
00:13:10,333 --> 00:13:11,067
Is that so?

262
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:13,600
Why me?

263
00:13:13,733 --> 00:13:15,000
You're right there!

264
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:40,300
- Come on, Hey! Babe!
- That's enough!

265
00:13:40,433 --> 00:13:43,400
Oh, my, this is delicious,
grandchild.

266
00:13:43,533 --> 00:13:47,833
I hope you find your the one.

267
00:13:48,933 --> 00:13:51,800
Grandmother, I'm sure he's
in the other barangay.

268
00:13:53,067 --> 00:13:53,933
Are you sure?

269
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:56,900
Just kidding, Grandmother.

270
00:13:57,033 --> 00:13:59,833
You're too serious!

271
00:13:59,967 --> 00:14:00,900
- Just relax.
- No.

272
00:14:01,033 --> 00:14:04,567
I just don't want
to leave you alone.

273
00:14:06,133 --> 00:14:08,233
I'll be so sad.

274
00:14:08,367 --> 00:14:08,933
Grandmother!

275
00:14:09,067 --> 00:14:10,400
That's a long time,

276
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:12,167
Grandmother you're still so
strong.

277
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:14,300
We have all the time
in the world.

278
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:16,100
And that's what I want too.

279
00:14:16,233 --> 00:14:20,567
I'm sure I'll find a man who
will be with me

280
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:23,033
and who won't leave me no matter
what.

281
00:14:23,167 --> 00:14:25,033
Hey, I hope so, grandchild.

282
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:38,333
What I hate most is someone
who hurts women!

283
00:14:38,467 --> 00:14:39,667
Excuse me.

284
00:14:42,467 --> 00:14:46,667
You have no right to hurt
my lovey doves!

285
00:14:48,567 --> 00:14:49,900
You want to interfere?

286
00:14:51,733 --> 00:14:52,467
Go, baby!

287
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:54,333
Nice one, lovey doves!

288
00:14:55,433 --> 00:14:58,600
Grandmother, your maintenance,
I need to buy.

289
00:14:58,733 --> 00:15:00,367
Leave it alone.
I have another one.

290
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:03,133
What are you going to drink
tomorrow, okay?

291
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:05,367
- I'll buy it. No.
- I'll buy it, huh?

292
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:07,167
Wait a minute,
wait a minute.

293
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:07,800
Why?

294
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:08,933
Aren't you going to change?

295
00:15:09,067 --> 00:15:11,167
Maybe later they'll insult you
again outside.

296
00:15:11,733 --> 00:15:13,033
Don't they dare!

297
00:15:14,167 --> 00:15:15,933
Bring an umbrella.

298
00:15:16,067 --> 00:15:17,700
Maybe the rain will catch you
there.

299
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:20,400
It's just so close. I'll just
hurry. I'll be right back.

300
00:15:20,533 --> 00:15:21,800
The pharmacy is
right there, oh.

301
00:15:21,933 --> 00:15:26,200
She's so stubborn, just like me.

302
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:28,367
Thank you.

303
00:15:29,667 --> 00:15:30,767
Okay, thank you.

304
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:40,800
Enriquez, two bottles?
I'm here at 171.

305
00:15:40,933 --> 00:15:42,967
What happened here
with Mr. Mean?

306
00:15:44,233 --> 00:15:45,400
Two bottles...

307
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:51,100
that's just so close.

308
00:15:57,833 --> 00:16:00,433
- Go babe.
- Go love.

309
00:16:00,667 --> 00:16:03,200
I knew it you couldn't
resist me, honey.

310
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:05,500
Come on!

311
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:08,633
What happened to your smile?

312
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:11,167
I don't want you anymore!

313
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:12,533
Yuck, yuck, yuck!

314
00:16:12,667 --> 00:16:13,433
Honey!

315
00:16:13,567 --> 00:16:14,100
Yuck! Yuck!

316
00:16:14,233 --> 00:16:15,967
Lovey doves!

317
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:19,700
Because of you,
I lost my girlfriend!

318
00:16:21,467 --> 00:16:22,267
Hey!

319
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,200
Hey, stop that!
I'm a police officer!

320
00:16:24,333 --> 00:16:27,600
Police, hey, police!
That's enough!

321
00:16:27,733 --> 00:16:28,833
- Come on! That's enough!
- What's up?

322
00:16:28,967 --> 00:16:30,133
Police! Police!

323
00:16:32,967 --> 00:16:33,633
Sir...

324
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:35,367
Sir Tonyo!

325
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,067
Hey, what did you do to our
deliveries?

326
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:38,000
Mister, help me!

327
00:16:38,133 --> 00:16:39,367
Miss, pay for all of this!

328
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:40,567
Why me?

329
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:42,333
Well, you're the only one
with that man.

330
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:43,733
Pay for all of that!

331
00:16:43,867 --> 00:16:44,500
What?

332
00:16:44,633 --> 00:16:45,333
Otherwise, I'll call the police.

333
00:16:45,467 --> 00:16:46,100
Call the police.

334
00:16:46,233 --> 00:16:47,367
Pay for all of that!

335
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:52,633
Here it is.

336
00:16:52,933 --> 00:16:55,067
Please just check if the money
was transferred already.

337
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:56,833
Yes, it was succefully
transferred.

338
00:16:56,967 --> 00:16:57,867
Next time,

339
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,467
tell your boyfriend not
to get drunk here.

340
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,233
He's not my boyfriend...

341
00:17:06,167 --> 00:17:09,900
Miss, can you help me call
a tricycle?

342
00:17:10,033 --> 00:17:11,233
You can do that alone.

343
00:17:11,367 --> 00:17:12,433
You're a nuisance.

344
00:17:13,467 --> 00:17:14,800
She's so grumpy.

345
00:17:18,033 --> 00:17:19,667
Sir, where should I take you?

346
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:33,733
Okay, it's just near.

347
00:17:33,867 --> 00:17:35,233
Come on, Sir.

348
00:17:37,167 --> 00:17:38,033
Sir.

349
00:17:40,733 --> 00:17:41,867
Sir, come on.

350
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,167
Where are we going?

351
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:47,900
Your jacket.

352
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:52,533
- You're so heavy.
- Where are we going?

353
00:17:52,667 --> 00:17:53,700
What do you mean where are we
going?

354
00:17:53,833 --> 00:17:56,100
Come on! Let's go home.

355
00:18:04,033 --> 00:18:05,667
Ma'am, we're here, Ma'am.

356
00:18:06,933 --> 00:18:08,733
The road is closed.

357
00:18:08,867 --> 00:18:10,067
I think they're working on it.

358
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:14,333
What now? What?
Isn't there another road?

359
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:15,433
Nothing, Ma'am.

360
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:17,700
My God. Is it still far?

361
00:18:17,833 --> 00:18:19,100
Yes, it's still far, Ma'am.

362
00:18:20,733 --> 00:18:22,433
Mister, is it okay if you just
come with me?

363
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:23,900
We'll bring him home.

364
00:18:24,033 --> 00:18:25,300
That's fine, Ma'am.

365
00:18:25,433 --> 00:18:26,833
Just add 500.

366
00:18:26,967 --> 00:18:27,700
What?

367
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:31,333
Never mind.

368
00:18:33,733 --> 00:18:35,200
Lieutenant Conde, come on.

369
00:18:45,767 --> 00:18:47,567
Oh my.

370
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:48,800
Ma'am, Ma'am, wait a minute.

371
00:18:48,933 --> 00:18:49,500
What?

372
00:18:49,633 --> 00:18:50,667
Your payment.

373
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:53,300
Sorry, Mister.

374
00:18:56,233 --> 00:18:58,567
You're so pretty,
but you're not going to pay.

375
00:19:02,267 --> 00:19:03,933
My God.

376
00:19:04,067 --> 00:19:04,900
Oh my.

377
00:19:06,967 --> 00:19:08,533
Where is that?

378
00:19:12,467 --> 00:19:13,300
There, there.

379
00:19:13,433 --> 00:19:14,533
There, 41.

380
00:19:16,667 --> 00:19:17,333
Oh, wait.

381
00:19:17,467 --> 00:19:18,133
Sir...

382
00:19:19,467 --> 00:19:20,767
The key, Sir?

383
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:28,800
That's Tonyo?

384
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,867
It's Tonyo.

385
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,333
Who's with him?

386
00:19:35,467 --> 00:19:37,933
Don't take it personally, Sir.

387
00:19:38,067 --> 00:19:39,200
Wait.

388
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:40,433
There, oh!

389
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:49,300
It looks like Tonyo will
be fighting tonight.

390
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:52,967
Tonyo, my loves.

391
00:19:53,100 --> 00:19:54,033
There.

392
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,600
There's a lot!

393
00:20:05,233 --> 00:20:06,700
Come on. Oh, my God.

394
00:20:08,467 --> 00:20:09,967
Where is it?

395
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:16,700
Wait, wait, wait.

396
00:20:16,833 --> 00:20:18,033
Me first.

397
00:20:18,167 --> 00:20:19,367
Let's do this.

398
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:21,533
Let's do what Tonyo
and his companion will do.

399
00:20:21,667 --> 00:20:23,367
Come on, come on!

400
00:20:30,867 --> 00:20:32,267
Where's the light?

401
00:20:36,167 --> 00:20:37,167
Ouch.

402
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:38,167
Hey...

403
00:20:51,133 --> 00:20:51,867
Oh, my.

404
00:20:54,067 --> 00:20:55,333
You're so heavy, Sir.

405
00:20:55,467 --> 00:20:56,733
Lara...

406
00:20:58,133 --> 00:20:59,467
Lara...

407
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:03,467
I pity you, Sir.
No one's taking care of you.

408
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:09,200
Sir.

409
00:21:09,367 --> 00:21:13,300
I'll work my way here, okay?
I'll just get some medicine.

410
00:21:44,333 --> 00:21:46,433
Sir, let me just look here, Sir.

411
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,800
Your body is big, Sir.

412
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:55,700
Hey..

413
00:21:57,367 --> 00:22:00,867
I will not fall for you.

414
00:22:02,167 --> 00:22:04,867
Hey!

415
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,600
You talk as if...

416
00:22:06,733 --> 00:22:08,067
What did you say?

417
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,700
Feeling?

418
00:22:09,833 --> 00:22:12,300
My wife will be angry.

419
00:22:15,367 --> 00:22:17,733
Lara will be angry.

420
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,967
Sir, do you have a band-aid?

421
00:22:31,300 --> 00:22:33,100
Let me just check what you have,
Sir.

422
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,067
That's it.

423
00:23:13,633 --> 00:23:14,733
Sorry.

424
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:29,733
I guess you're okay now.

425
00:23:29,867 --> 00:23:30,933
I'm going home, Sir.

426
00:23:32,067 --> 00:23:34,000
Maybe my Grandmother is waiting
for me.

427
00:23:35,633 --> 00:23:36,467
Okay, Sir.

428
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,667
What's that?
The rain is so heavy!

429
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,233
Oh my.

430
00:23:50,367 --> 00:23:52,567
I should have listened
to Grandmother!

431
00:23:57,833 --> 00:23:59,400
Sir...

432
00:23:59,533 --> 00:24:01,300
I'll just wait for the rain
to stop, okay?

433
00:24:02,867 --> 00:24:04,233
I might get sick.

434
00:24:06,033 --> 00:24:08,333
Don't worry.
I won't do anything to you.

435
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:16,167
Grandmother.

436
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:18,200
Where is Bobby?

437
00:24:18,333 --> 00:24:20,167
It's raining hard outside.

438
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:21,033
Yes, Grandmother.

439
00:24:21,167 --> 00:24:23,600
She went out to buy my medicine.

440
00:24:30,033 --> 00:24:31,567
I'll eat some more rice, okay?

441
00:24:31,700 --> 00:24:32,733
Oh, grandchild.

442
00:24:32,867 --> 00:24:33,900
I'll finish this.

443
00:24:34,033 --> 00:24:35,400
- Where are you?
- Bobby?

444
00:24:35,533 --> 00:24:38,300
Grandmother,
I'm here at Lieutenant Conde.

445
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:42,433
I'm here at Lieutenant Conde's
house.

446
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:49,900
Bobby, why? How did that happen?

447
00:24:50,033 --> 00:24:50,933
What's with you?

448
00:24:51,067 --> 00:24:53,267
Bobby, spill the tea.

449
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:55,433
I went to him at the convenience
store,

450
00:24:55,567 --> 00:24:58,367
and then I just saw him
on the floor, unconscious,

451
00:24:58,500 --> 00:24:59,667
badly beaten.

452
00:25:00,833 --> 00:25:02,567
So I brought him home here.

453
00:25:02,733 --> 00:25:05,867
It's annoying because they made
me pay for all the damage

454
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:07,133
he did there.

455
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:09,800
You'll pay for it all.

456
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:13,233
Grandchild, I'm telling you.

457
00:25:13,367 --> 00:25:14,367
You'll remember.

458
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:17,867
Yes, Grandmother,
I'll be careful.

459
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:18,867
Oh, no, no!

460
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,567
I don't want to!
Don't be careful!

461
00:25:20,700 --> 00:25:21,800
I don't want to!

462
00:25:21,933 --> 00:25:24,633
I want to have a grandchild!

463
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:27,867
We'll be the godfathers!

464
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:30,100
- Yes, me too.
- Right?

465
00:25:30,233 --> 00:25:31,200
What's that?

466
00:25:31,333 --> 00:25:32,767
Stop it!

467
00:25:32,900 --> 00:25:34,833
Come on, Grandmother.

468
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,200
I'll go home.

469
00:25:36,333 --> 00:25:38,100
I'll wait for the rain
to stop here.

470
00:25:38,233 --> 00:25:39,467
Okay, Grandmother.

471
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:42,167
- Good night. Bye.
- Bye.

472
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:43,900
Don't send Bobby home,
Grandmother.

473
00:25:44,033 --> 00:25:47,900
- Don't do it. What happened?
- Go ahead! What's that?

474
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:49,833
I can't sleep over this.

475
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:53,367
It seems like she has
surrendered herself!

476
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:18,000
Sir Tonyo is fine, right?

477
00:26:18,133 --> 00:26:19,900
He looks fragrant. Wow!

478
00:26:20,033 --> 00:26:22,000
My opinion of Sir Tonyo
has changed.

479
00:26:22,133 --> 00:26:25,000
I just can't imagine his life
now that he's home alone.

480
00:26:25,133 --> 00:26:26,967
Do you want to talk about
what happened last night?

481
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:28,767
Nothing happened last night,
Sir.

482
00:26:28,900 --> 00:26:29,467
Are you sure?

483
00:26:29,600 --> 00:26:30,900
Yes, Sir, nothing!

484
00:26:31,033 --> 00:26:33,967
Make sure you two don't do
anything stupid today

485
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:35,733
because the Mayor will award
you.

486
00:26:35,867 --> 00:26:37,533
Award? What for?

487
00:26:37,667 --> 00:26:38,967
You're too much.

488
00:26:39,100 --> 00:26:39,700
What's that?

489
00:26:39,833 --> 00:26:41,000
Your seatbelt.

490
00:26:41,133 --> 00:26:42,867
You know, Enriquez,
in our line of work,

491
00:26:43,033 --> 00:26:44,700
feelings shouldn't prevail.

492
00:26:44,833 --> 00:26:45,833
Feelings?

493
00:26:45,967 --> 00:26:46,967
I don't have feelings, Sir?

494
00:26:47,100 --> 00:26:48,800
There's a newcomer
at Station 12.

495
00:26:48,933 --> 00:26:51,267
You're the one suspected
of being behind the chaos

496
00:26:51,400 --> 00:26:52,533
that's happening.

497
00:26:52,667 --> 00:26:54,133
Sergeant Enriquez.

498
00:26:54,267 --> 00:26:57,533
I want the police to
take their eyes off me,

499
00:26:57,667 --> 00:26:59,700
especially Sergeant Enriquez.

500
00:26:59,833 --> 00:27:00,800
Get down!
